meta {
  name: Analyze Behavioral Session
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: {{KEYSTROKE_BASE_URL}}/api/keystroke/analyze
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{ACCESS_TOKEN}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "sessionId": "session-001",
    "studentId": "{{CURRENT_USER_ID}}",
    "events": [],
    "finalCode": "def hello():\n    print('Hello world')\n\nhello()",
    "includeReport": true
  }
}

docs {
  Comprehensive behavioral analysis of a complete coding session.

  Analyzes the full event stream (keystroke events captured during a coding session)
  and the final submitted code to produce:

  - Developmental logic & iteration score
  - Cognitive load timeline
  - Authenticity indicators (copy/paste detection, AI-assistance flags)
  - Friction point map (places where the student struggled)
  - Pedagogical recommendations for the instructor

  Set includeReport: true to receive a human-readable markdown report alongside
  the structured JSON analysis object.

  When GEMINI_API_KEY is configured the analysis is enriched with LLM-powered
  qualitative insights (gemini-2.5-flash). Without the key the service falls back
  to heuristic analysis only.
}
